  "2": "Feature",
  "3": "Tool Function Calling",
  "4": "Model Context Protocol (MCP)",
  "5": "Standardization Proprietary and",
  "6": "vendor-specific. The format",
  "7": "and implementation differ",
  "8": "across LLM providers.",
  "9": "An open, standardized protocol,",
  "10": "promoting interoperability",
  "11": "between different LLMs and tools.",
  "12": "Scope",
  "13": "A direct mechanism for an",
  "14": "LLM to request the",
  "15": "execution of a specific,",
  "16": "predefined function.",
  "17": "A broader framework for how",
  "18": "LLMs and external tools discover",
  "19": "and communicate with each",
  "20": "other.",
  "21": "Architecture",
  "22": "A one-to-one interaction",
  "23": "between the LLM and the",
  "24": "application's tool-handling",
  "25": "logic.",
  "26": "A client-server architecture where",
  "27": "LLM-powered applications",
  "28": "(clients) can connect to and utilize",
  "29": "various MCP servers (tools).",
  "30": "Discovery",
  "31": "The LLM is explicitly told",
  "32": "which tools are available",
  "33": "within the context of a",
  "34": "specific conversation.",
  "35": "Enables dynamic discovery of",
  "36": "available tools. An MCP client can",
  "37": "query a server to see what",
  "38": "capabilities it offers.",
  "39": "Reusability",
  "40": "Tool integrations are often",
  "41": "tightly coupled with the",
  "42": "specific application and",
  "43": "LLM being used.",
  "44": "Promotes the development of",
  "45": "reusable, standalone \"MCP",
  "46": "servers\" that can be accessed by",
  "47": "any compliant application.",
  "48": "Think of tool function calling as giving an AI a specific set of custom-built tools, like a",
  "49": "particular wrench and screwdriver. This is efficient for a workshop with a fixed set of",
  "50": "tasks. MCP (Model Context Protocol), on the other hand, is like creating a universal,",
  "51": "standardized power outlet system. It doesn't provide the tools itself, but it allows any",
  "52": "compliant tool from any manufacturer to plug in and work, enabling a dynamic and",
  "53": "ever-expanding workshop.",
